The paper deals with the combinatorial properties of locally repairable codes, which are used in distributed data storage. The paper specifically uses matroid theory to analyze the properties of these codes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
